<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<body style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;max-width:640px;margin:0 auto;padding:24px;color:#222;">
  <h2 style="margin-bottom:4px;">Castability — Daily Signups Report</h2>
  <p style="color:#666;margin-top:0;"><%= @date_str %></p>
  <table style="background:#f5f5f5;border-radius:8px;padding:16px;width:100%;margin-bottom:24px;border-collapse:collapse;">
    <tr><td style="padding:6px 16px 6px 0;color:#666;font-size:14px;">New profiles today</td><td style="font-size:14px;"><strong><%= @new_signups_count %></strong></td></tr>
    <tr><td style="padding:6px 16px 6px 0;color:#666;font-size:14px;">New subscribers / conversions today</td><td style="font-size:14px;"><strong><%= @new_subs_count %></strong></td></tr>
    <tr><td style="padding:6px 16px 6px 0;color:#666;font-size:14px;">New Actor ID range today</td><td style="font-size:14px;"><strong><%= @id_range %></strong></td></tr>
    <tr><td style="padding:6px 16px 6px 0;color:#666;font-size:14px;">Highest Actor ID on platform right now</td><td style="font-size:14px;"><strong><%= @max_actor_id %></strong></td></tr>
    <tr><td style="padding:6px 16px 6px 0;color:#666;font-size:14px;">Yesterday's highest Actor ID</td><td style="font-size:14px;"><strong><%= @prev_max_actor_id %></strong></td></tr>
  </table>
  <div style="background:#fff8e1;border-left:4px solid #f5a623;padding:16px 20px;border-radius:4px;margin-bottom:24px;">
    <p style="margin:0 0 8px 0;font-weight:bold;font-size:15px;">📊 What this tells us — read this first</p>
    <p style="margin:0 0 10px 0;font-size:14px;line-height:1.6;">Actor IDs are assigned in order like ticket numbers — higher number means more recent signup. By comparing yesterday's highest ID to today's we can estimate total new signups even if some didn't fully complete their profile yet.</p>
    <% gap = @max_actor_id - @prev_max_actor_id %>
    <% matches = @new_signups_count %>
    <% discrepancy = gap - matches %>
    <% confidence = if discrepancy == 0 then 'HIGH ✅' elsif discrepancy.abs <= 2 then 'HIGH ✅ (minor rounding)' elsif discrepancy.abs <= 5 then 'MEDIUM ⚠️' else 'LOW ❌ — please check' end %>
    <table style="border-collapse:collapse;width:100%;font-size:14px;margin-bottom:10px;">
      <tr><td style="padding:4px 12px 4px 0;color:#555;">Highest ID yesterday</td><td><strong><%= @prev_max_actor_id %></strong></td></tr>
      <tr><td style="padding:4px 12px 4px 0;color:#555;">Highest ID today</td><td><strong><%= @max_actor_id %></strong></td></tr>
      <tr style="border-top:1px solid #ddd;"><td style="padding:6px 12px 6px 0;color:#555;">ID gap (estimated new signups)</td><td><strong><%= gap %></strong></td></tr>
      <tr><td style="padding:4px 12px 4px 0;color:#555;">Profiles captured in this report</td><td><strong><%= matches %></strong></td></tr>
      <tr><td style="padding:4px 12px 4px 0;color:#555;">Difference</td><td><strong><%= discrepancy == 0 ? 'None — exact match' : "#{discrepancy.abs} #{discrepancy > 0 ? 'missing from report' : 'extra in report'}" %></strong></td></tr>
      <tr style="border-top:1px solid #ddd;"><td style="padding:6px 12px 6px 0;color:#555;font-weight:bold;">Confidence rating</td><td style="font-weight:bold;"><%= confidence %></td></tr>
    </table>
    <% if discrepancy > 2 %>
    <div style="background:#fff3cd;border:1px solid #ffc107;border-radius:4px;padding:10px 14px;font-size:13px;margin-top:8px;">
      <strong>⚠️ Taylor — please double-check this.</strong><br><br>
      The ID gap says <strong><%= gap %> new signups</strong> happened today but this report only captured <strong><%= matches %></strong>. That's a difference of <strong><%= discrepancy %></strong>.<br><br>
      <strong>How to check (takes about 30 seconds):</strong>
      <ol style="margin:8px 0 0 0;padding-left:18px;line-height:1.8;">
        <li>Go to <a href="https://castability.gojilabs.app/admin/actors">castability.gojilabs.app/admin/actors</a></li>
        <li>Sort by "Date Created" — newest first</li>
        <li>Look for Actor IDs between <strong><%= @prev_max_actor_id %></strong> and <strong><%= @max_actor_id %></strong></li>
        <li>Any IDs in that range not in the CSV are the missing ones</li>
      </ol><br>
      Most likely causes: someone signed up but didn't finish their profile, a test account, or a signup that was immediately deleted. Mention it to Cronin if something looks genuinely off.
    </div>
    <% elsif discrepancy == 0 %>
    <p style="margin:8px 0 0 0;font-size:13px;color:#2e7d32;">✅ <strong>The numbers match exactly.</strong> You're good — the CSV has everything.</p>
    <% else %>
    <p style="margin:8px 0 0 0;font-size:13px;color:#e65100;">⚠️ <strong>Small difference of <%= discrepancy.abs %>.</strong> Likely a test account or timing edge. Probably fine — check the admin link above in 30 seconds if you want to be sure.</p>
    <% end %>
  </div>
  <p style="font-size:14px;margin-bottom:4px;"><strong>Attached CSV</strong> has every profile captured today — name, email, Actor ID, whether they're a paying subscriber or free/trial, and the exact time they signed up (UTC).</p>
  <p style="font-size:13px;color:#666;">Sort by "Actor ID" to see signups in the order they happened. The lowest ID = first person who signed up today.</p>
  <hr style="border:none;border-top:1px solid #eee;margin:24px 0;">
  <p style="font-size:11px;color:#aaa;margin:0;">Sent automatically at 7am PT · Platform max Actor ID at send time: <%= @max_actor_id %> · Questions? Contact Cronin.</p>
</body>
</html>
